quran[202]{c,v,t}:
  23,1,HAPPY now the BELIEVERS
  23,2,Who humble them in their prayer
  23,3,And who keep aloof from vain words
  23,4,And who are doers of alms deeds
  23,5,And who restrain their appetites
  23,6,"Save with their wives, or the slaves whom their right hands possess: for in that case they shall be free from blame"
  23,7,But they whose desires reach further than this are transgressors
  23,8,And who tend well their trusts and their covenants
  23,9,And who keep them strictly to their prayers
  23,10,These shall be the heritors
  23,11,"Who shall inherit the paradise, to abide therein for ever"
  23,12,Now of fine clay have we created man
  23,13,"Then we placed him, a moist germ, in a safe abode"
  23,14,"Then made we the moist germ a clot of blood: then made the clotted blood into a piece of flesh; then made the piece of flesh into bones: and we clothed the bones with flesh: then brought forth man of yet another make - Blessed therefore be God, the most excellent of Makers"
  23,15,Then after this ye shall surely die
  23,16,Then shall ye be waked up on the day of resurrection
  23,17,"And we have created over you seven heavens: - and we are not careless of the creation"
  23,18,"And we send down water from the Heaven in its due degree, and we cause it to settle on the earth; - and we have power for its withdrawal"
  23,19,"And by it we cause gardens of palm trees, and vineyards to spring forth for you, in which ye have plenteous fruits, and whereof ye eat"
  23,20,And the tree that groweth up on Mount Sinai; which yieldeth oil and a juice for those who eat
  23,21,"And there is a lesson for you in the cattle: We give you to drink of what is in their bellies, and many advantages do ye derive from them, and for food they serve you"
  23,22,And on them and on ships are ye borne
  23,23,"We sent Noah heretofore unto his people, and he said, \"O my people! serve God: ye have no other God than He: will ye not therefore fear Him"
  23,24,"But the chiefs of the people who believed not said, \"This is but a man like yourselves: he fain would raise himself above you: but had it pleased God to send, He would have sent angels: We heard not of this with our sires of old"
  23,25,Verily he is but a man possessed; leave him alone therefore for a time
  23,26,"He said, \"O my Lord! help me against their charge of imposture"
  23,27,"So we revealed unto him, \"Make the ark under our eye, and as we have taught, and when our doom shall come on, and the earth's surface shall boil up, Carry into it of every kind a pair, and thy family, save him on whom sentence hath already passed: and plead not with me for the wicked, for they shall be drowned"
  23,28,"And when thou, and they who shall be with thee, shall go up into the ark; say, 'Praise be unto God, who hath rescued us from the wicked folk"
  23,29,"And say, 'O my Lord! disembark me with a blessed disembarking: for thou art the best to disembark"
  23,30,"Verily in this were signs, and verily we made proof of man"
  23,31,We then raised up other generations after them
  23,32,"And we sent among them an apostle from out themselves, with, \"Worship ye God! ye have no other God than He: will ye not therefore fear Him"
  23,33,"And the chiefs of His people who believed not, and who deemed the meeting with us in the life to come to be a lie, and whom we had richly supplied in this present life, said, \"This is but a man like yourselves; he eateth of what ye eat, And he drinketh of what ye drink"
  23,34,"And if ye obey a man like yourselves, then ye will surely be undone"
  23,35,"What! doth he foretell you, that after ye shall be dead and become dust and bones, ye shall be brought forth"
  23,36,"Away, away with his predictions"
  23,37,"There is no life beyond our present life; we die, and we live, and we shall not be quickened again"
  23,38,"This is merely a man who forgeth a lie about God: and we will not believe him"
  23,39,"He said, \"O my Lord! help me against this charge of imposture"
  23,40,"He said, \"Yet a little, and they will soon repent them"
  23,41,"Then did the shout of the destroying angel in justice surprise them, we made them like leaves swept down by a torrent. Away then with the wicked people"
  23,42,Then raised we up other generations after them
  23,43,"Neither too soon, nor too late, shall a people reach its appointed time"
  23,44,"Then sent we our apostles one after another. Oft as their apostle presented himself to a nation, they treated him as a liar; and we caused one nation to follow another; and we made them the burden of a tale. Away then with the people who believe not"
  23,45,"Then sent we Moses and his brother Aaron, with our signs and manifest power"
  23,46,"To Pharaoh and his princes; but they behaved them proudly, for they were a haughty people"
  23,47,"And they said, \"Shall we believe on two men like ourselves, whose people are our slaves"
  23,48,And they treated them both as impostors; wherefore they became of the destroyed
  23,49,And we gave Moses the Book for Israel's guidance
  23,50,"And we appointed the Son of Mary, and His mother for a sign; and we prepared an abode for both in a lofty spot, quiet, and watered with springs"
  23,51,"O ye apostles! eat of things that are good: and do that which is right: of your doings I am cognisant"
  23,52,"And truly this your religion is the one religion; and I am your Lord: therefore fear me"
  23,53,"But men have rent their great concern, one among another, into sects; every party rejoicing in that which is their own"
  23,54,"Wherefore leave them till a certain time, in their depths of error"
  23,55,"What! think they that what we largely, bestow on them of wealth and children"
  23,56,"We hasten to them for their good? Nay, they have no knowledge"
  23,57,But they who are awed with the dread of their Lord
  23,58,And who believe in the signs of their Lord
  23,59,And who join no other gods with their Lord
  23,60,And who give that which they give with hearts thrilled with dread because they must return unto their Lord
  23,61,"These hasten after good, and are the first to win it"
  23,62,"We will not burden a soul beyond its power: and with us is a book, which speaketh the truth; and they shall not be wronged"
  23,63,"But as to this Book, their hearts are plunged in error, and their works are far other than those of Muslims, and they will work those works"
  23,64,Until when we lay hold on their affluent ones with punishment; lo! they cry for help
  23,65,"Cry not for help this day, for by Us ye shall not be succoured"
  23,66,"Long since were my signs rehearsed to you, but ye turned back on your heels"
  23,67,"Puffed up with pride, discoursing foolishly by night"
  23,68,Do they not then heed the things spoken - whether that hath come to them which came not to their fathers of old
  23,69,Or do they not recognise their apostle; and therefore disavow him
  23,70,"Or say they, \"A Djinn is in him?\" Nay! he hath come to them with the truth; but the truth do most of them abhor"
  23,71,"But if the truth had followed in the train of their desires, the heavens and the earth, and all that therein is, had surely come to ruin! But we have brought them their warning; and from their warning they withdraw"
  23,72,"Dost thou ask them for remuneration? But, remuneration from thy Lord is best; and He is the best provider"
  23,73,And thou indeed biddest them to the right path
  23,74,"But verily they who believe not in the life to come, from that path do surely wander"
  23,75,"And if we had taken compassion on them, and relieved them from their trouble, they would have plunged on in their wickedness, wildly wandering"
  23,76,"We formerly laid hold on them with chastisement, yet they did not humble them to their Lord, nor did they abase them"
  23,77,"Until, when we have opened upon them the door of a severe punishment, lo! they are in despair at it"
  23,78,"It is He who hath implanted in you hearing, and sight, and heart; how few of you give thanks"
  23,79,"It is He who hath caused you to be born on the earth: and unto Him shall ye be gathered"
  23,80,"And it is He who maketh alive and killeth, and of Him is the change of the night and of the day: Will ye not understand"
  23,81,"But they say, as said those of old"
  23,82,"They say,\"What! When we shall be dead, and have become dust and bones, shall we, indeed, be waked to life"
  23,83,"This have we been promised, we and our fathers aforetime: but it is only fables of the ancients"
  23,84,"SAY: Whose is the earth, and all that is therein; - if ye know"
  23,85,"They will answer, \"God's.\" SAY: Will ye not, then reflect"
  23,86,"SAY: Who is the Lord of the seven heavens, and the Lord of the glorious throne"
  23,87,"They will say, \"They are God's\". SAY: Will ye not, then, fear Him"
  23,88,"SAY: In whose hand is the empire of all things, who protecteth but is not protected? if ye know"
  23,89,"They will answer, \"In God's.\" SAY: How, then, can ye be so spell-bound"
  23,90,"Yea, we have brought them the truth; but they are surely liars"
  23,91,"God hath not begotten offspring; neither is there any other God with Him: else had each god assuredly taken away that which he had created, and some had assuredly uplifted themselves above others! Far from the glory of God, be what they affirm of Him"
  23,92,"He knoweth alike the unseen and the seen: far be He uplifted above the gods whom they associate with Him"
  23,93,"SAY: O my Lord! If thou wilt let me witness the infliction of that with which they have been threatened"
  23,94,O my Lord! place me not among the ungodly people
  23,95,"Verily, we are well able to make thee see the punishment with which we have threatened them"
  23,96,"Turn aside evil with that which is better: we best know what they utter against thee"
  23,97,"And SAY: \"O my Lord! I betake me to Thee, against the promptings of the Satans"
  23,98,"And I betake me to Thee, O my Lord! that they gain no hurtful access to me"
  23,99,"When death overtaketh one of the wicked, he saith, \"Lord, send me back again"
  23,100,"That I may do the good which I have left undone.\" \"By no means.\" These are the very words which he shall speak: But behind them shall be a barrier, until the day when they shall be raised again"
  23,101,"And when the trumpet shall be sounded, the ties of kindred between them shall cease on that day; neither shall they ask each other's help"
  23,102,"They whose balances shall be heavy, shall be the blest"
  23,103,"But they whose balances shall be light, - these are they who shall lose their souls, abiding in hell for ever"
  23,104,"The fire shall scorch their faces, and their lips shall quiver therein"
  23,105,What! Were not my signs rehearsed unto you? and did ye not treat them as lies
  23,106,"They shall say, \"O our Lord! our ill-fortune prevailed against us, and we became an erring people"
  23,107,"O our Lord! Bring us forth hence: if we go back again to our sins, we shall indeed be evil doers"
  23,108,"He will say; \"Be ye driven down into it; and, address me not"
  23,109,"A part truly of my servants was there, who said, \"O our Lord! we believe: forgive us, then, and be merciful to us, for of the merciful art thou the best"
  23,110,"But ye received them with such scoffs that they suffered you to forget my warning, and ye laughed them to scorn"
  23,111,"Verily this day will I reward then, for their patient endurance: the blissful ones shall they be"
  23,112,"He will say, \"What number of years tarried ye on earth"
  23,113,"They will say, \"We tarried a day, or part of a day; but ask the recording angels"
  23,114,"God will say, \"Short indeed was the time ye tarried, if that ye knew it"
  23,115,"What! Did ye then think that we had created you for pastime, and that ye should not be brought back again to us"
  23,116,"Wherefore let God be exalted, the King, the Truth! There is no god but He! Lord of the stately throne"
  23,117,"And whoso, together with God, shall call on another god, for whom he hath no proof, shall surely have to give account to his Lord. Aye, it shall fare ill with the infidels"
  23,118,"And SAY: \"O my Lord, pardon, and have mercy; for of those who show mercy, art thou the best"
  24,1,"A SURA which we have sent down and sanctioned! Clear signs have we sent down therein, that ye may take warning"
  24,2,"The whore and the whoremonger - scourge each of them with an hundred stripes; and let not compassion keep you from carrying out the sentence of God, if ye believe in God and the last day: And let some of the faithful witness their chastisement"
  24,3,The whoremonger shall not marry other than a whore or an idolatress; and the whore shall not marry other than a whoremonger or an idolater. Such alliances are forbidden to the faithful
  24,4,"They who defame virtuous women, and bring not four witnesses, scourge them with fourscore stripes, and receive ye not their testimony for ever, for these are perverse persons"
  24,5,"Save those who afterwards repent and live virtuously; for truly God is Lenient, Merciful"
  24,6,"And they who shall accuse their wives, and have no witnesses but themselves, the testimony of each of them shall be a testimony by God four times repeated, that he is indeed of them that speak the truth"
  24,7,"And the fifth time that the malison of God be upon him, if he be of them that lie"
  24,8,"But it shall avert the chastisement from her if she testify a testimony four times repeated, by God, that he is of them that lie"
  24,9,"And a fifth time to call down the wrath of God on her, if he have spoken the truth"
  24,10,"And but for the goodness and mercy of God towards you, and that God is He who loveth to turn, Wise"
  24,11,"Of a truth, they who advanced that lie were a large number of you; but regard it not as an evil to you. No, it is an advantage to you. To every man among them shall it be done according to the offence he hath committed; and as to that person among them who took on himself to aggravate it, a sore punishment doth await him"
  24,12,"Did not the faithful of both sexes, when ye heard of this, form a favourable judgment in their own minds, and say, \"This is a manifest lie"
  24,13,"Have they brought four witnesses of the fact? If they cannot produce the witnesses, they are the liars in the sight of God"
  24,14,"And but for the goodness of God towards you, and His mercy in this world and in the next, a severe punishment had come upon you for that which ye spread abroad"
  24,15,"when ye uttered with your tongues, and spake with your mouths that of which ye had no knowledge. Ye deemed it to be a light matter, but with God it was a grave one"
  24,16,"And did ye say when ye heard it, \"It is not for us to talk of this affair! O God! By thy Glory, this is a gross calumny"
  24,17,"God hath warned you that ye go not back to the like of this for ever, if ye be believers"
  24,18,"And God maketh His signs clear to you: for God is Knowing, Wise"
  24,19,"But as for those who love that foul calumnies should go forth against those who believe, a grievous chastisement awaits them In this world and in the next. And God hath knowledge, but ye have not"
  24,20,"And but for the goodness of God towards you and His Mercy, and that God is Kind, Merciful"
  24,21,"O ye who believe! follow not the steps of Satan, for whosoever shall follow the steps of Satan, he will enjoin on him what is base and blameworthy; and but for the goodness of God towards you, and His mercy, no one of you had been cleansed for ever: but God maketh whom He will to be clean, and God Heareth, Knoweth"
  24,22,"And let not persons of wealth and means among you swear that they will not give to their kindred, to the poor, and to those who have fled their homes in the cause of God; let them rather pardon and pass over the offence. Desire ye not that God should forgive you? And God is Gracious, Merciful"
  24,23,"Verily, they who throw out charges against virtuous but careless women, who yet are believers, shall be cursed in this world and in the world to come; and a terrible punishment doth await them"
  24,24,"Their own tongues, and hands, and feet, shall one day bear witness against them of their own doings"
  24,25,"On that day will God pay them their just due, and they shall know that God is the clear Truth itself"
  24,26,"Bad women for bad men, and bad men for bad women; but virtuous women for virtuous men, and virtuous men for virtuous women! These shall be cleared from calumnies; theirs shall be forgiveness and an honourable provision"
  24,27,"O ye who believe! enter not into other houses than your own, until ye have asked leave, and have saluted its inmates. This will be best for you: haply ye will bear this in mind"
  24,28,"And if ye find no one therein, then enter it not till leave be given you; and if it be said to you, \"Go ye back,\" then go ye back. This will be more blameless in you, and God knoweth what ye do"
  24,29,"There shall be no harm in your entering houses in which no one dwelleth, for the supply of your needs: and God knoweth what ye do openly and what ye hide"
  24,30,Speak unto the believers that they restrain their eyes and observe continence. Thus will they be more pure. God is well aware of what they do
  24,31,"And speak to the believing women that they refrain their eyes, and observe continence; and that they display not their ornaments, except those which are external; and that they throw their veils over their bosoms, and display not their ornaments, except to their husbands or their fathers, or their husbands' fathers, or their sons, or their husbands' sons, or their brothers, or their brothers' sons, or their sisters' sons, or their women, or their slaves, or male domestics who have no natural force, or to children who note not women's nakedness. And let them not strike their feet together, so as to discover their hidden ornaments. And be ye all turned to God, O ye Believers! that it may be well with you"
  24,32,"And marry those among you who are single, and your good servants, and the handmaidens. If they are poor, God of His bounty will enrich them. God is all-bounteous, Knowing"
  24,33,"And let those who cannot find a match live in continence till God of His bounty shall enrich them. And to those of your slaves who desire a deed of manumission, execute it for them, if ye know good in them, and give them a portion of the wealth of God which He hath given you. Force not your female slaves into sin, in order that ye may gain the casual fruitions of this world, if they wish to preserve their modesty. Yet if any one compel them, then Verily to them, after their compulsion, will God be Forgiving, Merciful"
  24,34,"And now have we sent down to you clear signs, and an instance from among those who flourished before you, and a caution for the God-fearing"
  24,35,"God is the LIGHT of the Heavens and of the Earth. His Light is like a niche in which is a lamp - the lamp encased in glass - the glass, as it were, a glistening star. From a blessed tree is it lighted, the olive neither of the East nor of the West, whose oil would well nigh shine out, even though fire touched it not! It is light upon light. God guideth whom He will to His light, and God setteth forth parables to men, for God knoweth all things"
  24,36,"In the temples which God hath allowed to be reared, that His name may therein be remembered, do men praise Him morn and even"
  24,37,"Men whom neither merchandise nor traffic beguile from the remembrance of God, and from the observance of prayer, and the payment of the stated alms, through fear of the day when hearts shall throb and eyes shall roll"
  24,38,"That for their most excellent works may God recompense them, and of His bounty increase it to them more and more: for God maketh provision for whom He pleaseth without measure"
  24,39,"But as to the infidels, their works are like the vapour in a plain which the thirsty dreameth to be water, until when he cometh unto it, he findeth it not aught, but findeth that God is with him; and He fully payeth him his account: for swift to take account is God"
  24,40,"Or like the darkness on the deep sea when covered by billows riding upon billows, above which are clouds: darkness upon darkness. When a man reacheth forth his hand, he cannot nearly see it! He to whom God shall not give light, no light at all hath he"
  24,41,Hast thou not seen how all in the Heavens and in the Earth uttereth the praise of God? - the very birds as they spread their wings? Every creature knoweth its prayer and its praise! and God knoweth what they do
  24,42,"God's, the Kingdom of the Heavens and of the Earth: and unto God the final return"
  24,43,"Hast thou not seen that God driveth clouds lightly forward, then gathereth them together, then pileth them in masses? And then thou seest the rain forthcoming from their midst; and He causeth clouds like mountains charged with hail, to descend from the heaven, and He maketh it to fall on whom He will, and from whom He will He turneth it aside. - The brightness of His lightning all but taketh away the sight"
  24,44,God causeth the day and the night to take their turn. Verily in this is teaching for men of insight
  24,45,"And God hath created every animal of water. Some go upon the belly; some go upon two feet; some go upon four feet. God hath created what He pleased. Aye, God hath power over all things"
  24,46,Now have we sent down distinct signs. - And God guideth whom He will into the right path
  24,47,"For there are who say \"We believe on God and on the Apostle, and we obey;\" yet, after this, a part of them turn back. But these are not of the faithful"
  24,48,"And when they are summoned before God and His Apostle that He may judge between them, lo! a part of them withdraw"
  24,49,"But had the truth been on their side, they would have come to Him, obedient"
  24,50,"What! are they diseased of heart? Do they doubt? Are they afraid that God and His Apostles will deal unfairly with them? Nay, themselves are the unjust doers"
  24,51,"The words of the believers, when called to God and His Apostle that He may judge between them, are only to say, \"We have heard, and we obey:\" these are they with whom it shall be well"
  24,52,"And whoso shall obey God, and His Apostle, and shall dread God and fear Him, these are they that shall be the blissful"
  24,53,"And they have sworn by God, with a most solemn oath, that if thou give them the word, they will certainly march forth. Say: swear ye not: of more worth is obedience. Verily, God is well aware of what ye do"
  24,54,"SAY: Obey God and obey the Apostle. Suppose that ye turn back, still the burden of his duty is on him only, and the burden of your duty rests on you. If ye obey Him, ye shall have guidance: but plain preaching is all that devolves upon the Apostle"
  24,55,"God hath promised to those of you who believe and do the things that are right, that He will cause them to succeed others in the land, as He gave succession to those who were before them, and that He will establish for them that religion which they delight in, and that after their fears He will give them security in exchange. They shall worship Me: nought shall they join with Me: And whoso, after this, believe not, they will be the impious"
  24,56,"But observe prayer, and pay the stated alms, and obey the Apostle, that haply ye may find mercy"
  24,57,"Let not the Infidels think that they can weaken God on His own Earth: their dwelling place shall be the Fire! and right wretched the journey"
  24,58,"O ye who believe! let your slaves, and those of you who have not come of age, ask leave of you, three times a day, ere they come into your presence; - before the morning prayer, and when ye lay aside your garments at mid-day, and after the evening prayer. These are your three times of privacy. No blame shall attach to you or to them, if after these times, when ye go your rounds of attendance on one another, they come in without permission. Thus doth God make clear to you His signs: and God is Knowing, Wise"
  24,59,"And when your children come of age, let them ask leave to come into your presence, as they who were before them asked it. Thus doth God make clear to you his signs: and God is Knowing, Wise"
  24,60,"As to women who are past childbearing, and have no hope of marriage, no blame shall attach to them if they lay aside their outer garments, but so as not to shew their ornaments. Yet if they abstain from this, it will be better for them: and God Heareth, Knoweth"
  24,61,"No crime shall it be in the blind, or in the lame, or in the sick, to eat at your tables: or in yourselves, if ye eat in your own houses, or in the houses of your fathers, or of your mothers, or of your brothers, or of your sisters, or of your uncles on the father's side, or of your aunts on the father's side, or of your uncles on the mother's side, or of your aunts on the mother's side, or in those of which ye possess the keys, or in the house of your friend. No blame shall attach to you whether ye eat together or apart. And when ye enter houses, salute one another with a good and blessed greeting as from God. Thus doth God make clear to you His signs, that haply ye may comprehend them"
  24,62,"Verily, they only are believers who believe in God and His Apostle, and who, when they are with him upon any affair of common interest, depart not until they have sought his leave. Yes, they who ask leave of thee, are those who believe in God and His Apostle. And when they ask leave of Thee on account of any affairs of their own, then grant it to those of them whom thou wilt, and ask indulgence for them of God: for God is Indulgent, Merciful"
  24,63,"Address not the Apostle as ye address one another. God knoweth those of you who withdraw quietly from the assemblies, screening themselves behind others. And let those who transgress his command beware, lest some present trouble befall them, or a grievous chastisement befall them, hereafter"
  24,64,"Is not whatever is in the Heavens and the Earth God's? He knoweth your state; and one day shall men be assembled before Him, and He will tell them of what they have done: for God knoweth all things"
  25,1,"BLESSED be He who hath sent down AL FURKAN (the illumination) on his servant, that to all creatures he may be a warner"
  25,2,"His the Kingdom of the Heavens and of the Earth! No son hath He begotten! No partner hath He in his Empire! All things hath He created, and decreeing hath decreed their destinies"
  25,3,"Yet have they adopted gods beside Him which have created nothing, but were themselves created: And no power have they over themselves for evil or for good, nor have they power of death, or of life, or of raising the dead"
  25,4,"And the infidels say, \"This Koran is a mere fraud of his own devising, and others have helped him with it, who had come hither by outrage and lie"
  25,5,"And they say, \"Tales of the ancients that he hath put in writing! and they were dictated to him morn and even"
  25,6,"SAY: He hath sent it down who knoweth the secrets of the Heavens and of the Earth. He truly is the Gracious, the Merciful"
  25,7,"And they say, \"What sort of apostle is this? He eateth food and he walketh the streets! Unless an angel be sent down and take part in his warnings"
  25,8,"Or a treasure be thrown down to him, or he have a garden that supplieth him with food . . .\" and those unjust persons say, \"Ye follow but a man enchanted"
  25,9,"See what likenesses they strike out for thee! But they err, and cannot find their way"
  25,10,"Blessed be He who if he please can give thee better than that of which they speak - Gardens, 'neath which the rivers flow: and pavilions will He assign thee"
  25,11,"Aye, they have treated the coming of \"the Hour\" as a lie. But a flaming fire have we got ready for those who treat the coming of the Hour as a lie"
  25,12,"When it shall see them from afar, they shall hear its raging and roaring"
  25,13,"And when they shall be flung into a narrow space thereof bound together, they shall invoke destruction on the spot"
  25,14,"Call not this day for one destruction, but call for destructions many"
  25,15,"SAY: Is this, or the Paradise of Eternity which was promised to the God-fearing, best? Their recompense shall it be and their retreat"
  25,16,"Abiding therein for ever, they shall have in it all that they desire! It is a promise to be claimed of thy Lord"
  25,17,"And on the day when he shall gather them together, and those whom they worshipped beside God, he will say, \"Was it ye who led these my servants astray, or of themselves strayed they from the path"
  25,18,"They will say, \"Glory be to thee! It beseemed not us to take other lords than thee. But thou gavest them and their fathers their fill of good things, till they forgat the remembrance of thee, and became a lost people"
  25,19,"Then will God say to the Idolaters, \"Now have they made you liars in what ye say, and they have no power to avert your doom, or to succour you.\" whosoever of you thus offendeth, we will make him taste a great punishment"
  25,20,"Never have we sent Apostles before thee who ate not common food, and walked not the streets. And we test you by means of each other. Will ye be steadfast? Thy Lord is looking on"